cs.NI, cs.MA, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.CR 

The paper discusses the performance evaluation of LPWAN for mobile IoT, which involves wireless communication and network protocols. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves experimental studies, which could fall under cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper discusses the need for new protocols, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
